    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Long, fine, soft hair of Peruvian alpacas. The term may be used to refer to a style of fabric originally made from alpaca hair but now often made from mohair, Icelandic sheep wool, or English wool.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
